     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <head>To women that paint themselues.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>A Lome wall and painted face are one;</l>
      <l>For th'beauty of them both is quickly gone.</l>
      <l>When the lome is fallen of, then lathes appeare,</l>
      <l>So wrinkles in that face fro th'eye to th'eare.</l>
      <l>The chastest of your sex contemne these arts,</l>
      <l>And many that vse them, haue rid in carts.</l>
   </lg>
   <byline>Arthur Dowton.</byline>
</div>
